{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mat|20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":20,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":1,"text":"“For the kingdom of heaven is like a landowner who went out early in the morning to hire workers for his vineyard.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":2,"text":"After agreeing with the workers on one denarius, he sent them into his vineyard for the day.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":3,"text":"When he went out about nine in the morning, he saw others standing in the marketplace doing nothing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":4,"text":"He said to them, ‘You also go into my vineyard, and I’ll give you whatever is right.’ So off they went.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":5,"text":"About noon and about three, he went out again and did the same thing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":6,"text":"Then about five he went and found others standing around and said to them, ‘Why have you been standing here all day doing nothing?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":7,"text":"“ ‘Because no one hired us,’ they said to him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":8,"text":"When evening came, the owner of the vineyard told his foreman, ‘Call the workers and give them their pay, starting with the last and ending with the first.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":9,"text":"“When those who were hired about five came, they each received one denarius.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":10,"text":"So when the first ones came, they assumed they would get more, but they also received a denarius each.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":11,"text":"When they received it, they began to complain to the landowner:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":12,"text":"‘These last men put in one hour, and you made them equal to us who bore the burden of the day’s work and the burning heat.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":13,"text":"“He replied to one of them, ‘Friend, I’m doing you no wrong. Didn’t you agree with me on a denarius?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":14,"text":"Take what’s yours and go. I want to give this last man the same as I gave you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":15,"text":"Don’t I have the right to do what I want with what is mine? Are you jealous because I’m generous?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":16,"text":"“So the last will be first, and the first last.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":17,"text":"While going up to Jerusalem, Jesus took the twelve disciples aside privately and said to them on the way,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":18,"text":"“See, we are going up to Jerusalem. The Son of Man will be handed over to the chief priests and scribes, and they will condemn him to death.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":19,"text":"They will hand him over to the Gentiles to be mocked, flogged, and crucified, and on the third day he will be raised.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":20,"text":"Then the mother of Zebedee’s sons approached him with her sons. She knelt down to ask him for something.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":21,"text":"“What do you want?” he asked her.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":22,"text":"Jesus answered, “You don’t know what you’re asking. Are you able to drink the cup that I am about to drink?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":23,"text":"He told them, “You will indeed drink my cup, but to sit at my right and left is not mine to give; instead, it is for those for whom it has been prepared by my Father.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":24,"text":"When the ten disciples heard this, they became indignant with the two brothers.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":25,"text":"Jesus called them over and said, “You know that the rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them, and those in high positions act as tyrants over them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":26,"text":"It must not be like that among you. On the contrary, whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":27,"text":"and whoever wants to be first among you must be your slave;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":28,"text":"just as the Son of Man did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":29,"text":"As they were leaving Jericho, a large crowd followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":30,"text":"There were two blind men sitting by the road. When they heard that Jesus was passing by, they cried out, “Lord, have mercy on us, Son of David!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":31,"text":"The crowd demanded that they keep quiet, but they cried out all the more, “Lord, have mercy on us, Son of David!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":32,"text":"Jesus stopped, called them, and said, “What do you want me to do for you?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":33,"text":"“Lord,” they said to him, “open our eyes.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":20,"verse":34,"text":"Moved with compassion, Jesus touched their eyes. Immediately they could see, and they followed him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":20,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,8,9,13,16,17,20,22,23,24,29,32,33],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Parable of the Vineyard Workers"},{"beforeVerse":17,"text":"The Third Prediction of His Death"},{"beforeVerse":20,"text":"Suffering and Service"},{"beforeVerse":29,"text":"Two Blind Men Healed"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“For the kingdom of heaven is like a landowner who went out early in the morning to hire workers for his vineyard."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:24","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 21:28","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":28,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 21:33","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":33,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 13:24","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":24},{"label":"Mt 21:28","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":28},{"label":"Mt 21:33","book":"Mat","chapter":21,"verse":33}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"After agreeing with the workers on one denarius,"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"A denarius = one day’s wage, also in vv. 9,10,13"},{"kind":"text","text":" he sent them into his vineyard for the day. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"A denarius = one day’s wage, also in vv. 9,10,13"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When he went out about nine in the morning,"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit about the third hour"},{"kind":"text","text":" he saw others standing in the marketplace doing nothing. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Lit about the third hour"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He said to them, ‘You also go into my vineyard, and I’ll give you whatever is right.’ So off they went. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"About noon and about three,"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":3,"text":"Lit about the sixth hour and the ninth hour"},{"kind":"text","text":" he went out again and did the same thing. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":3,"text":"Lit about the sixth hour and the ninth hour"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:20:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then about five"},{"kin